snippet: Commandos and F.B.I. agents descended on the outskirts of Benghazi just after midnight local time on Monday; grabbed Ahmed Abu Khattala, the suspect; and raced away, said those briefed on the operation.
abstract: American commandos seize Ahmed Abu Khattala, man suspected of leading deadly attack on United States Mission in Benghazi, Libya; no shots are fired in operation, which take place on outskirts of Benghazi; capture ends manhunt that dragged on for nearly two years, and is breakthrough in finding perpetrators of episode that has been politically divisive from the start.

byline.original: By MICHAEL S. SCHMIDT, PETER BAKER and ERIC SCHMITT
byline.contributor: Charlie Savage contributed reporting from Washington, and David D. Kirkpatrick from Cairo.

lead_paragraph: Commandos and F.B.I. agents descended on the outskirts of Benghazi just after midnight local time on Monday; grabbed Ahmed Abu Khattala, the suspect; and raced away, said those briefed on the operation.
